1
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:12,667
I owe you my son's life.

2
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:18,867
Every parent just wants
their kid to be safe.

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,633
I only wish I could've given
that to mine.

4
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:25,833
Agnes. Agnes, girl!

5
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:27,533
Take a look!
It's your husband!

6
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:29,033
-I did the right thing...
- He's famous!

7
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:31,033
even if it meant facing backlash
 for rescuing

8
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:36,300
the son of the infamous scammer,
 Samuel Trinidad.

9
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:37,700
But don't worry.

10
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:40,033
I'll investigate this case.

11
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:42,367
That cop?

12
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:45,233
Make sure he doesn't find
any dirt on us.

13
00:00:45,367 --> 00:00:48,267
Does this have anything to do
with what your father did?

14
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:49,833
When he was still alive,

15
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:52,667
I only knew he was there
through his financial support.

16
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,500
But now that he's dead,

17
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:56,067
things have gotten even worse.

18
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,500
Because we're left suffering
from the consequences

19
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:58,767
of his mistakes.

20
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:02,067
You know, fathers can be
a real pain sometimes.

21
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:06,567
Zeke? Zeke!

22
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,167
Zeke?

23
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:10,067
Zeke, what did you--

24
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,267
Zeke! Zeke!

25
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:12,500
Zeke...

26
00:01:15,233 --> 00:01:17,567
You know, ever since
the scandal blew up,

27
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,667
they really haven't had
a moment of peace.

28
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,500
And I'm feeling kind of guilty.

29
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:23,733
Because I was one
of the angry ones.

30
00:01:23,867 --> 00:01:26,467
Isn't this the apartment
they just moved into?

31
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:29,200
Oh no, my love.
Everyone might come after them!

32
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,467
They're on their way!

33
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,733
They know where you live!

34
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:35,367
- Stop this!
- Hey, hey!

35
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,133
- Calm down!
- Drop your weapon!

36
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:48,500
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:08,633
- Return our money!
- Everyone, back off!

38
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:10,100
Let's talk things out!

39
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:13,600
- [OVERLAPPING SHOUTING]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:14,633
There she is!

41
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,833
You've been hiding here, huh?

42
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:17,767
You thought you could
get away from us?

43
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,267
I'm begging all of you!

44
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,867
Please leave us alone!

45
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,367
We didn't do anything wrong!

46
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:24,700
Please!

47
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:29,800
[OVERLAPPING SCREAMING]

48
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:31,667
That's enough! That's enough!

49
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,800
Just give it back!

50
00:02:32,933 --> 00:02:34,533
- We want our money!
- Stop it!

51
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:36,000
Stop making a scene!

52
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:39,633
We don't give a damn about
your grandson's kidnapping!

53
00:02:39,767 --> 00:02:41,500
Your family of scammers
deserves the worst!

54
00:02:41,633 --> 00:02:42,800
- Damn you!
- Hey!

55
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:45,533
- Enough of this!
- No, she needs to hear it!

56
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,000
Hey, watch your mouth!

57
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:49,067
- Please stop!
- I don't like your tone!

58
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,433
- Stop!
- Just go!

59
00:02:50,567 --> 00:02:52,333
You're all crossing the line!

60
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:55,533
Why involve
an innocent child?

61
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:56,967
For goodness's sake!

62
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:59,300
My grandson had nothing
to do with any of this!

63
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,367
I understand your frustrations
toward my late husband!

64
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:05,700
But we're not a family
of scammers!

65
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:09,333
Like all of you, we were
Mike Trinidad's victims, too!

66
00:03:09,467 --> 00:03:10,867
We're innocent people!

67
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,633
- Stop lying!
- How dare you!

68
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:14,667
- You're a damn liar!
- We don't believe you!

69
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:15,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,600
- Liar!
- Where's our money?

71
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,667
- Return it now!
- We need it back!

72
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,967
[OVERLAPPING SHOUTING]

73
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:23,200
Hey!

74
00:03:23,333 --> 00:03:25,700
Make way for the modern hero!

75
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,867
Pay your respects to him!

76
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,167
- Huh?
- You don't know him?

77
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,033
- Who?
- What--

78
00:03:31,167 --> 00:03:32,867
Who am I?
I'll be arresting anyone

79
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,800
who doesn't leave this place!

80
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:35,700
Scram!

81
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:38,200
[CROWD SCREAMING IN FEAR]

82
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:45,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:51,067
It's over now, ma'am.

84
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:03,733
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

85
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:05,500
You've scammed
far too many people

86
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:07,400
and made countless others cry.

87
00:04:07,533 --> 00:04:10,367
But the lies end here.

88
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:14,833
I know exactly what kind of
operation you've been running.

89
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:19,267
And how you turned scamming

90
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:20,700
into a full-pledged business.

91
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:22,900
So if you're one of them,

92
00:04:23,033 --> 00:04:24,000
you'd better get ready.

93
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:25,400
There's no escaping
your fate now.

94
00:04:25,533 --> 00:04:26,800
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,567
And this is why we need

96
00:04:29,733 --> 00:04:33,133
a new generation
of law enforcers.

97
00:04:33,267 --> 00:04:37,833
Resilient, principled,
and courageous.

98
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:40,600
Ready to take on crime head-on.

99
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:44,467
What we need is a new breed
of authorities

100
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,633
who are not going to back down

101
00:04:46,767 --> 00:04:50,067
and who are ready to dismantle
these crime groups

102
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,367
once and for all!

103
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,500
[REPORTER] As you may now,

104
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:54,233
Mike Trinidad's grandchild
was recently kidnapped,

105
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:57,300
and he was rescued
by PO2 Johnny Policarpio,

106
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,667
which caused his name to make
the rounds on social media.

107
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,567
Some netizens even
go as far as to believe

108
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:04,867
he possesses the qualities
you just listed.

109
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,200
A strong, no-nonsense
police officer.

110
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:10,600
[JOHNNY ON TELEVISION]
First of all, he's just a child.

111
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:13,333
He has nothing to do
with the mistakes

112
00:05:13,467 --> 00:05:15,267
of his father or grandfather.

113
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:18,700
Second, it's our duty
as police officers

114
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,500
to protect the innocent.

115
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:22,000
But don't worry.

116
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,033
I'll investigate this case.

117
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:28,600
And I won't stop

118
00:05:29,667 --> 00:05:34,767
until I find the mastermind
behind this kidnapping case.

119
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:39,733
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:05:39,867 --> 00:05:42,000
It's too early to tell,

121
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:47,033
but I want to see
how far he'll go.

122
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:49,433
[DOOR OPENS]

123
00:05:49,567 --> 00:05:50,800
Ma.

124
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,733
Good thing Boying
and Ismael were here.

125
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:57,367
And the cops came too.

126
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:00,733
Remember the one from
the station who saved King?

127
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:02,733
The one you argued with.

128
00:06:02,867 --> 00:06:05,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:07,533
[JOHNNY] I didn't hesitate
 when I saw the boy.

130
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:10,433
I knew he was in danger,
so I rescued him right away.

131
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:13,067
He's the reason this happened.

132
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,233
By trying to impress the media,

133
00:06:15,367 --> 00:06:17,767
he exposed us to the people
angry at Papa.

134
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:23,233
Samuel, it's one problem
after another.

135
00:06:23,367 --> 00:06:26,733
King just got kidnapped,
and now this.

136
00:06:26,867 --> 00:06:29,433
We might need to move again.

137
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:33,667
Don't worry, Mama.

138
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,533
I'll start looking
for a new place.

139
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:40,867
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:43,167
Where's Arissa, Ma?

141
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,367
She hasn't come home yet.
Maybe she's still at work.

142
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:52,167
I'm getting worried
about that kid.

143
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:57,767
Hey, I'll take this home
and wash it, okay?

144
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,967
Okay, you guys go home.
I'll lock up.

145
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:02,533
Weren't you the one
who opened today?

146
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:04,200
I'm fine. Go ahead.

147
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:05,900
- Are you sure?
- Just be careful.

148
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,500
- You too.
- Bye.

149
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:08,900
Bye.

150
00:07:15,067 --> 00:07:20,467
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:24,500
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

152
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,600
Hello?

153
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:30,733
Where are you?

154
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,400
Uh...

155
00:07:32,533 --> 00:07:33,433
I'm still at work.

156
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:36,000
There was a problem
with the inventory.

157
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:37,867
I won't be coming home tonight.

158
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:39,967
Are you okay?

159
00:07:41,433 --> 00:07:42,833
I'm okay.

160
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:46,533
Okay, just...

161
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:48,200
just take care, alright?

162
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:57,400
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:02,333
[MUSIC FADES]

164
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,633
Johnny, why did you do that?

165
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:09,833
Why did you do the interview?

166
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:11,333
Why not?

167
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:12,400
Because of what you did,

168
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:15,467
Mike Trinidad's victims
found Samuel's home.

169
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,300
His family got in trouble again.

170
00:08:17,433 --> 00:08:19,600
You couldn't even be happy
for me, could you?

171
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,033
I accomplished my mission,

172
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,967
of course I'd get recognized.

173
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,867
Doesn't that mean
anything to you?

174
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,633
Johnny,
this isn't just about you!

175
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:29,767
Who is it about, huh?!

176
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,267
Samuel again?!

177
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:34,933
Seriously! Why is he
more important to you?

178
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:36,400
Who's your husband, huh?

179
00:08:36,533 --> 00:08:39,067
Me, right? Isn't it me?

180
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,367
Tell me the truth.

181
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,833
Are you having
an affair with him?

182
00:08:42,967 --> 00:08:44,200
He's your lover, isn't he?

183
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,200
Admit it!

184
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,300
[SOBS]
Can you stop?!

185
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:51,100
I've had enough!

186
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:56,233
What makes you think
there's something between us?

187
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,300
Don't pin your mistakes on me.

188
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,533
That's what happens...

189
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,567
when you're haunted
by your own demons!

190
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:08,267
[HUFFING]

191
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,833
What?

192
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:11,800
You're angry because I'm right.

193
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:15,500
I thought cops
don't hurt people?

194
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,867
Aren't you supposed
to protect the innocent,

195
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,033
not harm them?

196
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:24,400
Fine.

197
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:27,533
If you're such a great cop,
investigate me.

198
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:36,533
And if you ever find anything
between me and Samuel,

199
00:09:36,667 --> 00:09:38,600
that's the only time
you can confront me.

200
00:09:38,733 --> 00:09:45,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:09:53,667 --> 00:09:56,467
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

202
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:58,967
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

203
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:07,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:15,533
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:19,633
Heads up, Dad's here.

206
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:25,300
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:26,400
Mmm!

208
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,967
- [CHLOE] Daddy!
- Hi, darling.

209
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:31,700
- Hi, Jacob!
- Dad.

210
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,633
- Start eating, dear.
- Sorry.

211
00:10:33,767 --> 00:10:35,233
I'm eating already.

212
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,167
I missed Leah's cooking.

213
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:39,300
It's okay. Help yourself.

214
00:10:42,633 --> 00:10:45,567
So, how's business?

215
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:48,533
I mean, Oriental Ridge Estates.

216
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:51,867
Good. Very good.

217
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,133
I'm glad to hear that
it's going smoothly.

218
00:10:55,267 --> 00:11:00,133
Maybe that will get
Leah to stay at home.

219
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:03,667
I don't understand
why you still let her work.

220
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:08,200
Dad, I'm a lawyer.

221
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:11,733
My job is serious.

222
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:15,067
Even though Jacob works hard,

223
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:17,933
nothing can stop me
from pursuing my career.

224
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,500
Okay. If you say so.

225
00:11:21,633 --> 00:11:22,900
[CHUCKLES]

226
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:24,733
- Please, join me.
- Let's eat.

227
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:26,567
- Let me serve you.
- Thanks.

228
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:32,233
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:36,467
Look at this one, bro.

230
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,000
It's clean. It looks safe.

231
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:40,067
It's located in
a gated subdivision.

232
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,800
It looks good.

233
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:45,833
I'll contact the landlord.

234
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:46,867
Alright.

235
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:50,367
Guys?

236
00:11:52,533 --> 00:11:53,600
Thank you.

237
00:11:56,033 --> 00:12:01,200
Even though my life's a mess
and my family's in trouble,

238
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:04,167
you never left our side.

239
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,167
Of course, brother.

240
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,167
[BOTTLE THUDS]

241
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:11,700
But are you sure you don't
want to go to the police?

242
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:15,500
You know who was behind
King's kidnapping.

243
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:17,233
That's the thing, bro.

244
00:12:17,367 --> 00:12:19,133
I want to,

245
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:24,067
but I can't file a report
without solid evidence.

246
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,533
Samuel is right.

247
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:27,700
They can't open a case
without proof.

248
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:30,133
The cops might end up
arresting him instead.

249
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:32,967
That's why...

250
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:37,933
all I can do is be careful.

251
00:12:39,233 --> 00:12:42,833
My enemies are
cunning and powerful.

252
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:45,833
There you go, son.

253
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,267
[SAMUEL SIGHS]

254
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:52,900
Dad?

255
00:12:53,767 --> 00:12:54,900
Yes, son?

256
00:12:56,033 --> 00:13:02,067
Was Mommy watching over me
when I was kidnapped?

257
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:06,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

258
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:07,967
Uh...

259
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,800
I think so.

260
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:13,700
[KING] Maybe that's why
the police found me.

261
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:15,800
Because of Mommy.

262
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:18,700
She's my guardian angel.

263
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:26,267
But I wish she were
still here

264
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:31,733
so I could hug her
whenever I'm scared.

265
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:34,467
[SAMUEL] Son...

266
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,167
I'm here.

267
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:38,633
Daddy's here.

268
00:13:38,767 --> 00:13:40,500
I'll hug you.

269
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:44,333
You also have Grandma Lolita
and Auntie Arissa.

270
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:46,400
Okay?

271
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:50,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:52,700
Alright. Go to sleep.

273
00:13:54,600 --> 00:14:01,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

274
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:22,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

275
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:32,867
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:14:54,633 --> 00:15:01,467
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:28,167
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:42,933
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [KING SOBBING]

279
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:46,067
[KING] Please help me, Dad!

280
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:48,100
Dad!

281
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:49,467
Help!

282
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:53,133
[SOBS] Dad! Dad!

283
00:15:53,267 --> 00:15:55,167
Dad! Help!

284
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:57,167
Dad!

285
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:59,367
Help me!

286
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,667
- [SAMUEL] Son!
- Dad!

287
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,933
- Dad!
- I'm here now.

288
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:04,567
- [METAL CHAINS RATTLING]
- [SOBBING CONTINUES]

289
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:10,267
Dad! Dad! Dad! Dad!

290
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:12,600
[KING SCREAMING]

291
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:14,433
King! King, dear!

292
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:16,867
Dad, they took me again!

293
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,000
- Huh?
- Dad!

294
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:20,100
- Calm down, dear.
- They took me again!

295
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:22,900
- King, Daddy's here for you.
- [SOBBING]

296
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:29,567
I want to fix the mess
my father caused,

297
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:32,800
but my family's already been
hurt too many times.

298
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:37,500
Even King can't sleep properly
because of trauma.

299
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:40,067
Why don't we reach out
to the authorities for help?

300
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:42,900
We can coordinate with the
Department of Judicial Affairs

301
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:45,433
or the National
Investigation Bureau.

302
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:47,433
We can request
a witness protection order

303
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:48,733
or a custody order.

304
00:16:48,867 --> 00:16:52,500
Roldan always manages to slip
through the cracks of the law.

305
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:55,300
It won't be surprising if some
authorities are protecting him.

306
00:16:55,433 --> 00:16:58,333
We don't know
who his accomplices are.

307
00:16:58,467 --> 00:17:01,967
It could just put our lives
in greater danger.

308
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,467
[PAENG] So, what now?

309
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:04,567
You'll just run away?

310
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:07,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

311
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:11,400
The longer this goes on,

312
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:13,867
the more questions
run through my head.

313
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,733
Why would Roldan send
Samuel to Oriental Ridge,

314
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:18,200
then kidnap his son?

315
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:20,367
What do they want from Samuel?

316
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:24,167
Colonel.

318
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:27,033
Do you think
the money that Mike took

319
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:28,400
is actually with Samuel?

320
00:17:28,533 --> 00:17:30,733
That's the only
logical explanation.

321
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:35,833
But if I'm right,
will Samuel help us?

322
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:38,533
Or will he run off
with the money?

323
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:40,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,567
No, Colonel.

325
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:45,000
Even when I first
met Samuel...

326
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:48,400
[SIGHS DEEPLY] I could tell
he's a good person.

327
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:51,967
I'm sure he'll choose to do
the right thing in the end.

328
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:55,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

329
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:58,167
I don't want to do this,
but I feel like...

330
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:03,467
I feel like this is what
I need to do for my family.

331
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,900
Bro, how about the money?

332
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:10,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

333
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:14,400
I'll still return the money
to the victims.

334
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,433
I just need to make sure
my family's safe

335
00:18:17,567 --> 00:18:20,933
from the hands of Roldan.

336
00:18:21,067 --> 00:18:22,833
We need to get far away.

337
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,300
I need a clean escape.

338
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:26,833
No screw-ups.

339
00:18:26,967 --> 00:18:28,367
No noise.

340
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,067
Okay.

341
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,533
But you can no longer use
your real names

342
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:36,167
because you're already
on the watch list.

343
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:40,767
Bro, I know someone who
can forge IDs and passports.

344
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:42,967
Whatever documents you need.

345
00:18:46,067 --> 00:18:53,133
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

346
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:57,400
Bro, I have to go.

347
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:58,600
My condolences.

348
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,833
[SORROWFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

349
00:19:00,967 --> 00:19:05,167
[SNIFFLING]

350
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:11,233
- [SOBBING LOUDLY]
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

351
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:12,400
[SNIFFLES]

352
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,333
[SNIFFLES]

353
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:18,567
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

354
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,333
[SNIFFLES] Dear.

355
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:25,067
Dear, why didn't you
wait for Papa?

356
00:19:26,067 --> 00:19:29,800
[SNIFFLES]
I was looking for a solution.

357
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:32,000
I was looking for a way.

358
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:33,867
[SNIFFLES]

359
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,600
Papa will find a way.

360
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:41,000
- [SNIFFLING]
- [SORROWFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

361
00:19:41,133 --> 00:19:44,567
Why did it have to come to this?

362
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:46,167
Why?

363
00:19:47,267 --> 00:19:48,433
[SOBS]

364
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:50,400
Please forgive me, dear.

365
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:52,567
Please forgive me.

366
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:55,367
Please forgive Papa.

367
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:57,867
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

368
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,367
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:01,700
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

370
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,400
Mike Trinidad...

371
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:06,333
...and his son.

372
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:08,500
They're the ones
responsible for this.

373
00:20:08,633 --> 00:20:11,767
[SNIFFLES, SIGHS DEEPLY]

374
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,233
They ki--

375
00:20:13,367 --> 00:20:15,933
They killed you.
[SNIFFLES]

376
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:18,367
They killed you, dear.

377
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:25,333
[SULLEN MUSIC SWELLS]

378
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,300
This Thursday...

379
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:37,233
You're early.

380
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,000
That's what you do
when you love your job.

381
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:40,667
You're excited to go to work.

382
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,633
Remember this face.

383
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:45,167
This is the face
of the people you scammed!

384
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,233
Anton's not here yet.

385
00:20:46,367 --> 00:20:48,733
Why aren't you answering
your phone, Arissa?

386
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:51,533
A father lost his child
because of you!

387
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:52,933
Welcome to--

388
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,567
Agnes, we'll just have
a lunch meeting.

389
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:58,233
I was hoping
I'd find evidence against--

390
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,367
Get out of there.

391
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,867
They're coming back.
